Version 0.2: Speed Improvement
------------------------------
The link ordering now has a workaround. The throughput is now
roughly half that of ftp, which isn't bad given the protocol design.

Version 0.1: First release of Brf
---------------------------------
Most of the file-related syscalls have shim functions.
There are a small number of tiny utilities. The protocol runs over TCP.
There is an issue with link ordering which prevents Brf
from being linked with the C library.
